parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak from Fuel Tank or Fuel Pump Module
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak can cause a fire hazard, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. It can also cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: Strong fuel odor
fuel leak from the top of the tank
fuel dripping onto the ground
fuel spray or puddle under the vehicle
difficulty starting the vehicle
hesitation while driving
and fuel fumes entering the vehicle through the ventilation system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag sensor can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger airbag light stays on
the airbag does not turn on when a passenger is sitting in the seat
the airbag turns on and off intermittently
the service airbag light comes on
and the airbag display on the dash goes on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, which can lead to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
the airbag does not deploy in the event of an accident
and the airbag deploys without warning or impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and airbag system can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of an accident, which can lead to serious injury or death, and can also cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
and the airbag warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump module can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Strong gasoline odor inside and outside the vehicle
fuel leaks
difficulty starting the vehicle
sputtering or choking when accelerating or driving uphill.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to seize or become extremely hard to turn, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering fails intermittently
the steering wheel seizes or becomes hard to turn
the stabilitrak warning light illuminates
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the stabilitrak system can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The stabilitrak warning light illuminates
the vehicle is difficult to maneuver
the power steering fails
the vehicle loses traction and stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition and key system can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to start, increasing the risk of accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the key will not come out of the ignition when turning off the vehicle
the vehicle is difficult to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Concentric Slave Cylinder Failure and Clutch Master Cylinder Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the concentric slave cylinder or clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's speed, fuel level, and temperature, which can lead to accidents or engine damage.
symptoms: The speedometer
fuel gauge
and temperature gauge do not function properly
the odometer reading is stuck
the gauges may work intermittently or not at all.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the key to become stuck in the ignition, making it difficult or impossible to remove the key, which can lead to safety issues and potential theft.
symptoms: The key becomes stuck in the ignition
the key is difficult to remove from the ignition
the ignition switch makes a clicking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air bag sensor can cause the air bag to deploy unnecessarily or not deploy in the event of a crash, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The air bag light illuminates
the air bag sensor fails to detect the presence of a passenger
the air bag deploys unnecessarily.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal sticks
the brake lights illuminate
the vehicle loses braking power
the brake master cylinder needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speedometer can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's speed, which can lead to accidents or traffic violations.
symptoms: The speedometer reading is inaccurate
the speedometer needle jumps or sticks
the speedometer fails to function.
